 of various places called Montfort in France (from Old French <i>mont</i> ‘hill’ + <i>fort</i> ‘fortress’). Early forms of this name are indistinguishable from those of Mundford in Norfolk, perhaps indicating an alternative habitational name (see   Munford  ).","History: A Norman bearer of this name, from Montfort-sur-Risle in Eure, near Brionne, accompanied William the Conqueror in his invasion of England in 1066. Simon <i>de Montfort</i>, 6th Earl of Leicester, led a rebellion against Henry III (1216–1272)."]}]},{"name":"Osbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old English personal name derived from <i>ōs</i> ‘god’ + <i>beorht</i> ‘bright, famous’. It is not now common, but in the earlier 20th century it enjoyed a modest vogue in Britain, being borne for example by the cartoonist  Osbert Lancaster  (  1908–86 ) and the writer  Osbert Sitwell  (  1892–1969 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Osbert de Mundeford I was born about 1200, in Mundford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom as the son of Adam de Mundeford I. He married Mary in 1240, in United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1272, in his hometown, at the age of 73."},"et":{"about 1200–1272":"umbes 1200–1272","1200–1272":"1200–1272","1240–1272":"1240–1272","1242–1256":"1242–1256","1170–1234":"1170–1234","1234":"1234","1256":"1256","1200":"1200","1242":"1242","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1240":"1240","1272":"1272","about 1240":"umbes 1240","after 1256":"pärast 1256","1170":"1170","Mundeford,Norfolk,England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mundham, Norfolk, England":"Mundham, Norfolk, England","Mundeford's Manor, Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, England","Mundford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Mundford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mundford, Norfolk, England":"Mundford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Grande-Bretagne":"United Kingdom"},"f